<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Huege</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-29 11:28:21</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Trust me stamina helps.  Its just it seems there are cut-off points.  When I first played this game i used a human warrior with all of his stamina equipment he only had something like 106.  Currently I play an ogre warrior with which I've concentrated on stamina and agility (after AC of course)  After a guildmate of mine gave me a bracer of scavanging I've finally capped my stamina out at 200.  Let me give an example of the difference.  My human warrior never got very high in level so this is a low level analogy.  At level 19 my human had mid 500s for hp, I think.  My ogre surpassed him at level 13.(the gap just keeps growing, at 19 I was mid 800s, its amazing when you compare your hp with level 30 and 40 friends, now I'm talking other tanks, and say wow my hp is gonna catch yours in 5 levels)  That with a combination of high agility and a high base strength keeps me in battle for the longest possible and I can still out muscle those wimpy elves.  Item procs and dex kiss me arse doesn't help so much when your dead does it?  Oh yeah and I can hold my breath for a long while, not that thats too important.</font></td></tr></table>
